(8/12) Can you imagine what the mass was like on Pulag’s summit? The wind-blown clouds made haste to escort the sun down while temperatures dropped. In his homily, @PNPCordillera Chaplain Fr. Jonathan Chy talked about how Jesus would go to the mountains to pray. ???? https://t.co/fMswYxo5zR

(7/12) HHWATMPS (Holding hands while at the Mt. Pulag Summit) w/ the @pnpcordillera RD ?An outdoors guy, the hubby trekked Pulag twice. When I say I can’t do something, he pushes me beyond my comfort zone. I guess he’s proud of me for climbing Pulag&Ulap in the span of 7days?? https://t.co/39mfA1xMAB

(6/12) The thing about a hike is the people you’re with: the hubby & 2 of our kids, Zoe & Zed. The hubby’s aide de camp, Lt. Byron Dulansi. Our close-in: Mike, Brent, Gyver & Archie. Capt Marnie Abellanida who sang “Salidumay”. & Lt Elisa Enriquez who was my hike buddy. https://t.co/XjPT7LP7Fj

(5/12) With every step I took, there was plenty of time to reflect: Just keep going. Put one foot in front of the other, & the nearer you are to your destination on both a mountain trail & in life. Not everything has to be perfect, planned down to the minutest detail. Chill. ?? https://t.co/xBXuMep49e

(4/12) The beauty of Pulag? The soft crunch of combat boots & hiking shoes on the trail. Leaves & twigs crackling. Stones laid out like art in the grasslands. Clean air in an 11,300 hectare natl park. Cotton clouds covering the sun. A little bit of heaven on God’s good earth? https://t.co/OR8x8vWZLP

(3/12) I’d say Pulag was easier on me than Mt Ulap was. Ulap’s descent was treacherous. Pulag’s Ambangeg trail is a longer trek but both ascent & descent were slow & easy. I thought: “What was I thinking. Hiking two mountains in just a span of one week on the day I turned 54.  ? https://t.co/ICH6frydbl

(2/12) Mayor Faustino Aquisan of Kabayan, Benguet and the barangay captain, Kapitan Efren Tellama, welcomed us so graciously. @PNPCordillera & @PNPBenguet_PPO were the advance party & security for the visit of DENR Usec. Leonardo for work to protect Mt. Pulag National Park. ?? https://t.co/Zl1vEN6Fyd

(1/12) Grateful to have gone w/ hubby, @PNPCordillera Reg’l Director, Gen. Rwin Pagkalinawan on a patrol of majestic MtPulag, the highest peak in Luzon. Reached the summit4:30pm. Sermon&sunset on the mount in the great Cordillera outdoors made Mar10 a joyful 54thbday for me? ? https://t.co/jJF2Yov2fl

Even my Ateneo College batch 88 reunion - which is supposed to be an annual thing & will be timed with christmas - will be virtual. I’m sure many of you have made the same “virtual” plans for christmas. Because... again, why risk it? And for what?

The @DOHgovph itself said in a Nov 9 press release to limit get togethers “preferably to people within the same household.” and we all know what that means, yes? Lets listen to the doctors and the health experts.

My family - Hontiveros siblings, cousins, nephews & nieces - already decided that we’ll have a virtual reunion. And my siblings & I & our mom will not get together either. We each have our own household “bubbles” to protect. Covid is out there. Be smart about things.

As the pandemic stretches on and enters its 8th month, which just so happens to be a month away from Christmas, some of you may feel pressured by others to “do some unsafe celebrating.” Its okay to say “no”. Because, really, who wants to put themselves and their families at risk? https://t.co/gGwSt8uFxM
